{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012QM38wz6mmHtoZQEF57iht","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"category\":{\"name\":\"Ideas\"},\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/dsyme/charset_normalizer/discussions/9\",\"number\":9,\"title\":\"Daily Perf Improver - Research and Plan\",\"created_at\":\"2025-10-15T17:38:28Z\",\"body\":\"# Daily Perf Improver - Performance Research and Plan\\n\\n## Executive Summary\\n\\ncharset_normalizer is a Python library for charset/encoding detection that prioritizes **both accuracy and performance** over its main competitor (chardet). The project already has strong performance foundations with mypyc compilation, existing benchmarks, and a comprehensive test suite. This research identifies specific optimization opportunities across algorithm efficiency, build performance, and developer workflow improvements.\\n\\n## Current Performance Landscape\\n\\n### ‚úÖ Existing Strengths\\n\\n**1. Performance Testing Infrastructure**\\n- Dedicated performance test script (`bin/performance.py`) comparing against chardet\\n- Benchmarks run on 400+ test files from char-dataset repository\\n- CI/CD integration with `nox -s performance` in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`\\n- Current metrics show **10x faster** than chardet (10ms vs 63ms mean, 100 file/sec vs 16 file/sec)\\n- Percentile tracking (50th, 95th, 99th) for performance distribution\\n\\n**2. Compilation Optimization**\\n- **mypyc integration** for Python-to-C compilation (setup.py:L8-28)\\n- Currently only compiles `src/charset_normalizer/md.py` (mess detection module)\\n- Environment variable `CHARSET_NORMALIZER_USE_MYPYC=1` controls compilation\\n- Cross-platform CI testing (Ubuntu, macOS, Windows) for mypyc builds\\n\\n**3. Type Safety \\u0026 Code Quality**\\n- Full mypy type annotations with strict configuration (pyproject.toml:L88-104)\\n- Pre-commit hooks with ruff, mypy, pyupgrade\\n- Comprehensive test coverage (92% requirement)\\n\\n### ÔøΩÔøΩ Performance Characteristics\\n\\n**Codebase Structure** (~4,630 lines total):\\n- `api.py` (669 lines): Main detection entry points\\n- `md.py` (635 lines): Mess detection plugins - **already mypyc compiled**\\n- `constant.py` (2,015 lines): Large encoding tables and language data\\n- `cd.py` (395 lines): Coherence detection (language detection)\\n- `utils.py` (414 lines): Helper functions\\n- `models.py` (360 lines): Data structures\\n\\n**Performance-Critical Paths**:\\n1. **Detection algorithm** (`api.py:from_bytes`): Iterates through IANA encodings, tests chunks\\n2. **Mess ratio calculation** (`md.py:mess_ratio`): Character-by-character analysis with 8 detector plugins\\n3. **Coherence ratio** (`cd.py:coherence_ratio`): Language detection using character frequency tables\\n4. **Chunk processing**: Configurable steps (default 5) and chunk_size (default 512 bytes)\\n\\n### üéØ Known Performance Concerns (from issues)\\n\\n1. **Small input performance** (#428, #566):\\n   - cchardet is 5-200x faster on very small inputs\\n   - charset_normalizer optimized for larger files (1MB+)\\n   - Trade-off: accuracy vs raw speed\\n\\n2. **Language detection overhead** (#389):\\n   - User reported wanting to disable language detection for performance\\n   - Suggestion: optional parameter to skip coherence ratio calculation\\n\\n3. **Build time** (#583, #595):\\n   - mypyc build dependencies (mypy) causing friction\\n   - Could affect development iteration speed\\n\\n## Performance Improvement Plan\\n\\n### Phase 1: Algorithm \\u0026 Core Performance üöÄ\\n\\n**Priority 1.1: Expand mypyc Compilation Coverage**\\n- **Impact**: Potential 2-10x speedup on hot paths (based on #182 results)\\n- **Effort**: Medium\\n- **Files to compile**:\\n  - `cd.py`: Coherence detection (language frequency lookups)\\n  - `utils.py`: Helper functions called frequently\\n  - `api.py`: Main detection loop (if type-compatible)\\n- **Validation**: Run `bin/performance.py` before/after, ensure accuracy maintained\\n\\n**Priority 1.2: Optimize Mess Detection Loop**\\n- **Target**: `md.py:mess_ratio` function (lines 583-635)\\n- **Opportunities**:\\n  - Currently iterates all 8 detector plugins for each character\\n  - Early exit optimization already present (threshold-based)\\n  - Consider: lazy plugin instantiation, plugin result caching\\n- **Measurement**: Profile with `cProfile` on large files\\n\\n**Priority 1.3: Small Input Fast Path**\\n- **Target**: Sequences \\u003c 100 bytes (#428, #509)\\n- **Approach**:\\n  - Add quick ASCII/UTF-8 detection for tiny inputs\\n  - Skip language detection for inputs \\u003c TOO_SMALL_SEQUENCE (32 bytes)\\n  - Limit encoding candidates tested\\n- **Success**: Competitive with cchardet on small inputs while maintaining accuracy\\n\\n**Priority 1.4: Optional Language Detection**\\n- **Feature**: Add `enable_language_detection` parameter (default True)\\n- **Impact**: Skip coherence_ratio calculation when not needed (#389)\\n- **Backward compatible**: Maintain existing behavior by default\\n\\n### Phase 2: Development Workflow Performance üõ†Ô∏è\\n\\n**Priority 2.1: Build System Optimization**\\n- **Issue**: mypyc compilation adds significant build time\\n- **Solutions**:\\n  - Document speedup techniques (pre-compiled wheels, incremental builds)\\n  - Consider optional mypyc: pure Python fallback for development\\n  - Investigate build caching strategies\\n- **Target**: Reduce developer rebuild time from cold start\\n\\n**Priority 2.2: Test Execution Performance**\\n- **Current**: Full test suite across multiple Python versions\\n- **Opportunities**:\\n  - Identify slow tests (pytest --durations=10 already used)\\n  - Consider test parallelization (pytest-xdist)\\n  - Optimize char-dataset cloning (noxfile.py uses shallow clone)\\n\\n**Priority 2.3: CI/CD Pipeline Efficiency**\\n- **Current state**: \\n  - Matrix testing: 8 Python versions (3.7-3.14) √ó 1 OS = 8 jobs\\n  - mypyc testing: 8 Python versions √ó 3 OS = 24 jobs\\n  - Total: ~32 jobs per PR\\n- **Optimization targets**:\\n  - Artifact caching between jobs\\n  - Conditional job execution (skip mypyc on docs-only changes)\\n  - Parallel workflow execution\\n\\n### Phase 3: Algorithm \\u0026 Data Structure Optimizations üßÆ\\n\\n**Priority 3.1: Encoding Table Lookup Performance**\\n- **File**: `constant.py` (2,015 lines of data)\\n- **Opportunity**: Analyze IANA_SUPPORTED list traversal in api.py\\n- **Potential**: Convert to set for O(1) membership testing where applicable\\n\\n**Priority 3.2: Chunk Processing Tuning**\\n- **Parameters**: steps (default 5), chunk_size (default 512)\\n- **Experiment**: Profile different configurations for common file sizes\\n- **Goal**: Find optimal defaults or adaptive strategies\\n\\n**Priority 3.3: Memory Efficiency**\\n- **Large file handling**: api.py uses lazy string decoding for files \\u003e= TOO_BIG_SEQUENCE\\n- **Review**: Memory usage patterns, potential for streaming API\\n\\n### Phase 4: Measurement \\u0026 Documentation üìà\\n\\n**Priority 4.1: Performance Profiling Guide**\\n- **Content**:\\n  - How to profile charset_normalizer locally\\n  - Using `bin/performance.py` effectively\\n  - Interpreting results (mean, percentiles, file-specific slowdowns)\\n  - Tools: cProfile, line_profiler, memory_profiler\\n\\n**Priority 4.2: Benchmark Suite Expansion**\\n- **Current**: Comparison with chardet only\\n- **Add**: \\n  - cchardet comparison (with caveats about different use cases)\\n  - More diverse test files (different sizes, encodings, languages)\\n  - Real-world scenario benchmarks (web scraping, file conversion)\\n\\n**Priority 4.3: Performance Regression Detection**\\n- **Goal**: Detect performance regressions in CI\\n- **Implementation**: \\n  - Store baseline metrics\\n  - Alert on significant slowdowns (e.g., \\u003e10% regression)\\n  - Track performance trends over releases\\n\\n## Success Metrics\\n\\n### Primary Metrics\\n1. **Throughput**: Files per second on char-dataset benchmark\\n2. **Latency**: Mean, 50th, 95th, 99th percentile execution time\\n3. **Accuracy**: Detection coverage percentage (maintain ‚â•97%)\\n4. **Build time**: Time to run `pip install -e .` (developer experience)\\n\\n### Secondary Metrics\\n1. **Test execution time**: `nox -s test` duration\\n2. **CI/CD duration**: Total workflow time\\n3. **Memory usage**: Peak RSS for large files\\n4. **Small file performance**: \\u003c 100 byte detection time\\n\\n## Risk Assessment \\u0026 Considerations\\n\\n**‚ö†Ô∏è Critical Constraints**:\\n- **Accuracy first**: Performance improvements must not reduce detection accuracy below current levels\\n- **Backward compatibility**: All optimizations must maintain existing API\\n- **Cross-platform**: Changes must work on Linux, macOS, Windows\\n- **Python version support**: 3.7-3.14 compatibility\\n\\n**‚ö†Ô∏è Known Challenges**:\\n- mypyc compilation complexity (build infrastructure, debugging)\\n- Trade-off between small vs large file performance\\n- Language detection accuracy vs speed trade-offs\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n\\n1. **Immediate**: Proceed to Phase 2 (build configuration \\u0026 guides)\\n2. **Quick wins**: Small input fast path (#509), optional language detection (#389)\\n3. **High impact**: Expand mypyc compilation to cd.py and utils.py\\n4. **Long term**: Comprehensive profiling and algorithm optimization\\n\\n## References\\n\\n- Performance comparison: README.md:L60-82\\n- Current benchmarks: bin/performance.py\\n- CI performance test: .github/workflows/ci.yml:L239-258\\n- mypyc integration: Issue #182 (2x speedup achieved on md.py)\\n- Small input concerns: Issues #428, #509\\n- Language detection overhead: Issue #389\\n- Build system: Issues #583, #595\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Generated by**: Daily Perf Improver workflow (Phase 1)  \\n**Date**: 2025-10-15  \\n**Status**: Awaiting maintainer review for Phase 2 execution\\n\\n\\n\\u003e AI generated by [Daily Perf Improver](https://github.com/dsyme/charset_normalizer/actions/runs/18537473696)\"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a28ae7c6-6784-4cca-9033-2f906ec425a5","uuid":"fb50f8b7-5a64-4c2f-90c9-a10cacfecc67"}
