d methodology\n- Documents before/after testing procedures\n- Covers profiling tools (cProfile, line_profiler, memory_profiler, py-spy)\n- Provides micro-benchmarking techniques\n- Defines performance reporting standards and acceptable thresholds\n\n## Rationale\n\nThese additions enable efficient performance engineering by:\n\n1. **Reproducible environment**: The build steps action ensures consistent setup across all performance work\n2. **Fast iteration**: Guides emphasize developing in pure Python and only compiling for benchmarks\n3. **Reliable measurements**: Comprehensive measurement methodology ensures valid performance comparisons\n4. **Knowledge preservation**: Guides document best practices so future work doesn't repeat mistakes\n\n## Testing Plan\n\n- [x] Build steps action syntax validated\n- [ ] Manual testing of build steps action (to be done by maintainer or in next workflow run)\n- [x] Guides reviewed for accuracy against existing codebase structure\n- [x] All file paths and commands verified against repository layout\n\n## Next Steps\n\nAfter this PR is merged, the Daily Perf Improver workflow will proceed to Phase 3, where it will:\n1. Execute the build steps to set up the environment\n2. Use these guides to efficiently identify and implement performance improvements\n3. Create PRs with measured performance optimizations\n\n## Request for Review\n\nPlease review:\n- Build steps action correctness (dependencies, installation order, logging)\n- Performance guides accuracy and completeness\n- Any project-specific considerations I should incorporate\n\n---\n\nü§ñ Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>","branch":"perf/daily-perf-improver-config-phase2"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":717,"cache_read_input_tokens":96635,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":717,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":9